Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.96,0:01:42.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.93,0:01:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.80,0:01:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, here he is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.10,0:01:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.36,0:02:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.76,0:02:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.76,0:02:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Here, I'll take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.53,0:02:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about the change.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.24,0:02:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't need to buy anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.45,0:02:43.39,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 2\NTwo Worlds
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.66,0:02:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.46,0:02:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. I was coming here anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.53,0:02:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I have to return your gloves.\NI'll get them for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.84,0:02:59.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.07,0:03:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll collect the gloves another time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.24,0:03:02.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.85,0:03:08.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to keep them.\NIn other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.52,0:03:11.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They'll be my excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.45,0:03:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need an excuse...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.69,0:03:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mistress would be\Npleased to see you anytime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.03,0:03:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? No, that's not what I meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.04,0:03:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.14,0:03:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if you wish to come again...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.45,0:03:45.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father is very angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.92,0:03:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He wants to know why you're\Noff gallivanting around instead of working.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.63,0:03:52.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I leave it in your capable hands, Teresa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.10,0:04:01.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Flattery won't help you. I can't\Nmake excuses for you every day!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.64,0:04:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's not as if I want to\Ncarry on my father's work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.31,0:04:09.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't say things like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.11,0:04:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Looks like someone's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.58,0:04:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're avoiding the subject again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.25,0:04:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.89,0:04:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.42,0:04:22.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother Will!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.03,0:04:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're home, brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.09,0:04:28.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, Vivi, Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.46,0:04:30.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Arthur's here too?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.50,0:04:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sound so pleased to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.93,0:04:35.00,Alternate,,0000,0000,0000,,We ran into him at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.01,0:04:38.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.41,0:04:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Stevens.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.61,0:04:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How was Lyme Regis?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.48,0:04:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I much prefer London.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.75,0:04:47.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but the country's better in some respects.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.32,0:04:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But in the country, there are no\Nshops or theatres. It was so boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.92,0:04:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.39,0:04:57.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother Will, I heard that Harrods has\Nbeen refurbished. Take me there!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.06,0:04:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.16,0:05:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some other time? And when would that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.63,0:05:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I said, some other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.50,0:05:05.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some other time never seems to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.61,0:05:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home, Colin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.02,0:05:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come in!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.46,0:06:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.26,0:06:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father wishes to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.37,0:06:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem you've turned down\Nevery invitation you've received.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.67,0:06:21.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moreover, you've left it to\NStevens to pen your regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.64,0:06:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.08,0:06:27.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the one who needs to apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.02,0:06:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.42,0:06:31.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were just so many.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.25,0:06:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We may not have a title, but do you know\Nwhy our merchant family receives invitations?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.36,0:06:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of our money?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.46,0:06:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is one reason. But we mustn't forget\Ncharacter, intelligence and manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.37,0:06:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the qualities valued by polite society.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.55,0:07:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The upper class is dependent upon\Npolite society. That is part of our work too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.62,0:07:10.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but I-
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.12,0:07:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You will go to the ball this evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.86,0:07:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told them you would be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.70,0:07:20.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.81,0:07:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lady Elliott...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.47,0:07:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and Miss Elliott.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.80,0:07:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use standing there like that, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.24,0:08:00.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Robert!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.94,0:08:04.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should dance with someone at least once.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.11,0:08:07.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I should.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.85,0:08:10.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But to be perfectly honest, it's a bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.95,0:08:12.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you come, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.17,0:08:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,William?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.70,0:08:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been such a long time, Mrs. Campbell!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.04,0:08:34.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It has indeed, William. I was worried\Nbecause I hadn't seen you lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.08,0:08:36.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.51,0:08:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is your father well?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.68,0:08:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm pleased to say he still\Nhas a lot to say for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.65,0:08:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew I should have worn my lace gloves...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.15,0:08:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this? You're still going on about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.79,0:08:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.56,0:08:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eleanor, introduce yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.50,0:09:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening. My name is Eleanor Campbell...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.40,0:09:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is William Jones. Delighted to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.01,0:09:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight is her first ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.28,0:09:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.48,0:09:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She doesn't like her dress, doesn't like her hair...\NShe's been complaining all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.99,0:09:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.66,0:09:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't mind, would you\Ndance one waltz with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.16,0:09:27.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.76,0:09:30.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you do me the honor\Nof a dance, Miss Campbell?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.37,0:09:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.62,0:09:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.85,0:09:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never would have thought\Nthis was your first dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.09,0:09:54.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you're a natural.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.80,0:10:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They certainly do make a handsome couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.42,0:10:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll hold this for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.09,0:10:28.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.19,0:10:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.16,0:10:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now. Don't be a nuisance to Miss Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.56,0:10:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, I don't know whether\Nyou're helping or hindering...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.83,0:10:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some potatoes, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.70,0:10:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I recommend the green beans today!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.94,0:10:41.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.17,0:10:44.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, some green beans please.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.01,0:10:45.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.77,0:10:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.44,0:10:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have two wonderful assistants.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.32,0:10:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, brother Will! Does it suit me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.15,0:11:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.66,0:11:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't even look.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.86,0:11:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure we should be here with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.03,0:11:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.13,0:11:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you have something else\Nthat you wanted to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.66,0:11:13.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. The three of us haven't\Nspent time together for ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.50,0:11:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the least I could do.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.94,0:11:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister, it's Eleanor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.44,0:11:24.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eleanor, it's been such a long time!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.78,0:11:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Grace!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.32,0:11:37.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How fortuitous that we should meet like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.69,0:11:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not really. All fashionable ladies shop\Nat the same stores, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.33,0:11:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.30,0:11:47.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.44,0:11:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Brother Will, do you know Eleanor?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.27,0:11:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We met at the ball the other night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.41,0:11:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.04,0:11:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, what a nice umbrella!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.11,0:11:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.88,0:12:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think they like each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.45,0:12:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivi!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.02,0:12:09.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you come here often?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.69,0:12:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I just wanted a parasol.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.53,0:12:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A parasol?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.06,0:12:18.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.10,0:12:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.13,0:12:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I try to coordinate my parasol with my dress\Neach day, so I'm always in need of a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.51,0:12:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.14,0:12:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. For example,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.38,0:12:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as you can see, some are\Ndecorated with lace or ribbons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.72,0:12:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And some of the handles are made from\Nivory or are intricately sculptured.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.59,0:12:41.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.34,0:12:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I admit they are rather lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.18,0:13:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would a lady be happy\Nto receive a present like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.08,0:13:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... she would.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.22,0:13:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.79,0:13:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh... b-but...!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.59,0:13:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to give this to a lady.\NCould you wrap it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.86,0:13:18.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.49,0:13:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Brother Will's going to\Nbuy a present for Eleanor?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.33,0:13:25.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean to imply that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.87,0:13:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?\NI didn't mean to imply that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.20,0:13:27.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.34,0:13:32.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, l...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.31,0:13:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean to imply\Nthat I wanted you to...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.25,0:13:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, for giving you\Nthe wrong impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.49,0:13:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was careless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.61,0:13:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...! Well then, who are you\Ngoing to give that parasol to, brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.96,0:13:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's none of your business.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.40,0:13:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivi, stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.13,0:13:59.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.16,0:15:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Eleanor, are you sure you\Ndidn't want to buy a parasol?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.40,0:15:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested in a parasol.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.64,0:15:47.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I heard this rumor...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.74,0:15:50.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that Master William has a lady friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.58,0:15:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.61,0:15:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Master William should\Nfall in love at first sight... I'm jealous!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.42,0:15:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But really, Master Arthur is more my type.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.12,0:15:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.05,0:16:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His moodiness just drives me wild!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.22,0:16:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.66,0:16:08.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop chattering and get on with your work!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.16,0:16:09.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:13.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are working hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.73,0:16:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's the housekeeper,\Nshe just wants to be bossy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.35,0:17:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.35,0:17:06.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.62,0:17:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came for my gloves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.36,0:17:15.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My gloves-
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.06,0:17:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.60,0:17:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.90,0:17:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.57,0:17:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.51,0:17:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma baked that scone, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.85,0:17:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It tastes good! Very, very good!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.69,0:17:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our Young Master is so\Naccustomed to a lavish lifestyle...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.46,0:17:48.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that he finds the homely taste refreshing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.86,0:17:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't mean it like that...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.70,0:17:53.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.30,0:17:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've run out of sugar, have we not?\NPlease go and buy some.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.54,0:18:00.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But ma'am, I haven't finished cleaning...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.74,0:18:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.58,0:18:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.55,0:18:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I'll go with her!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.92,0:18:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When The Season begins, there\Nseem to be more people in London.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.13,0:18:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, my brothers and sisters have\Njust returned from a health resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.07,0:18:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had to go shopping with\Nmy sisters. But you know what?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.80,0:18:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found a parasol that\NI thought would suit you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.94,0:18:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be very happy if you use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.45,0:18:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm honored, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.39,0:18:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I couldn't accept such a lavish present.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.16,0:18:54.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing, really. Please don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.70,0:18:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That may be so for you,\Nbut to me it's quite extravagant.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.47,0:19:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not something I could easily\Nafford, even if I worked hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.07,0:19:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have I upset you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.18,0:19:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no! I don't mean to be rude.\NBut, the lace handkerchief I received...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.55,0:19:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is more than enough.\NI don't wish for anything else...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.19,0:19:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize. I've acted poorly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.33,0:19:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your smile then, when you\Naccepted the lace handkerchief...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.50,0:19:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I just wanted to see it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.93,0:19:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.77,0:19:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.14,0:19:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't buy any more presents.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.41,0:19:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.31,0:19:45.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't we spend some time\Ntogether occasionally, like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.08,0:19:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.75,0:19:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm back, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.62,0:19:57.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, a pot of tea, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.43,0:19:59.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.19,0:20:29.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Young Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.56,0:20:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here, Teresa.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.06,0:20:34.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, sit down.\NYou can take that off now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.24,0:20:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a gift of thanks,\Nfor always putting up with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.37,0:20:46.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.04,0:20:48.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.55,0:20:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this? Such a fussy umbrella!\NI'm not a girl anymore, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.62,0:21:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.62,0:21:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it suits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.53,0:21:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.73,0:21:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, since it's a gift,\NI must accept it, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.58,0:21:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.14,0:21:52.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That parasol...!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.35,0:22:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Doesn't that woman\Nwork for the Jones family?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.07,0:24:08.94,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode:\NThe Confession
